                <div class="book-info">
                    <p><strong>Year of Publication:</strong> 1890</p>
                    <p><strong>Author:</strong> Oscar Wilde</p>
                    <p><strong>Synopsis:</strong> "The Picture of Dorian Gray" is a philosophical novel by Oscar Wilde. It tells the story of a young man named Dorian Gray who remains youthful and beautiful while a portrait of him ages and reflects his moral corruption. The novel explores themes of vanity, hedonism, and the consequences of one's actions.</p>
