                <div class="book-info">
                    <p><strong>Year of Publication:</strong> 2019</p>
                    <p><strong>Author:</strong> Camila Sosa Villada</p>
                    <p><strong>Synopsis:</strong> "Las Malas" is a novel by Argentine author Camila Sosa Villada. The book follows the lives of transgender women who work as sex workers in the city of Córdoba, Argentina. It explores their struggles, relationships, and dreams, offering a powerful portrayal of resilience and survival in the face of societal prejudice and discrimination.</p>
